cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on generating sentences from Abstract Meaning Representation (AMR) graphs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural network models, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the encoding of graphs, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of image data in some experiments, which could potentially place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
